# Format: one SHA-256 hash per line. Comments with # are allowed.
#
# Add a term:   python3 .ai/scripts/confidentiality-scanner.py --add "<term-to-block>"
# Remove term:  python3 .ai/scripts/confidentiality-scanner.py --remove "<term>"
# Check term:   python3 .ai/scripts/confidentiality-scanner.py --check-word "<term>"
#
# This .example file is committed to version control.
# The real blocklist (.ai/blocklist.sha256) is gitignored — it never leaves your machine.
#
# Bootstrap on a fresh checkout:
#   cp .ai/blocklist.sha256.example .ai/blocklist.sha256
#   python3 .ai/scripts/confidentiality-scanner.py --add "<term-from-secrets-manager-or-env>"
#
# Each hash below was generated with:
#   hashlib.sha256(term.lower().strip().replace("-","").replace("_","").encode()).hexdigest()
#
# No hashes are pre-populated in this example file.
# Add your organisation's prohibited terms once, then discard the plaintext.
